1
00:00:09,208 --> 00:00:11,000
[SHIBAKIYAMA] I'm thinking
the Dachi High team

2
00:00:11,083 --> 00:00:12,916
should come over and train
with us this weekend.

3
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:14,583
[BOTH gasp]

4
00:00:14,666 --> 00:00:15,833
[SHIBAKIYAMA] Wrestlers from
another stable are joining us

5
00:00:15,916 --> 00:00:17,625
for a joint training session.

6
00:00:17,708 --> 00:00:20,375
You'd also get a chance to fight
someone at the ozeki level.

7
00:00:20,458 --> 00:00:22,208
A real life ozeki?

8
00:00:26,125 --> 00:00:28,500
The Dachi High sumo club...

9
00:00:28,583 --> 00:00:30,416
has arrived in Nagoya!

10
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:34,833
Miso cutlets
and chicken wings, now!

11
00:00:34,916 --> 00:00:37,833
Settle down.
This isn't some pleasure cruise.

12
00:00:37,916 --> 00:00:40,500
Remember, we made this trip
so we could train.

13
00:00:40,583 --> 00:00:43,583
Looks like we arrived
way ahead of schedule.

14
00:00:43,666 --> 00:00:46,500
And the master's got a meeting,
so we won't see him till later.

15
00:00:46,583 --> 00:00:49,125
Fine. We'll have
our own team meeting then.

16
00:00:49,208 --> 00:00:51,000
Wha... Loosen up.

17
00:00:51,083 --> 00:00:52,875
I mean, come on!
We're in Nagoya, dude.

18
00:00:52,958 --> 00:00:54,416
Chihiro's got a point.

19
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:56,875
It won't hurt to save
the meeting for later tonight.

20
00:00:56,958 --> 00:00:58,833
I wanna see Nagoya Castle.

21
00:00:58,916 --> 00:01:00,375
The castle.

22
00:01:00,458 --> 00:01:01,791
Really?

23
00:01:01,875 --> 00:01:03,833
Could you please talk
some sense into them?

24
00:01:03,916 --> 00:01:05,458
Great idea.

25
00:01:05,541 --> 00:01:06,708
Let's go!

26
00:01:06,791 --> 00:01:07,875
Huh?!

27
00:01:07,958 --> 00:01:10,375
Making a quick detour
won't hurt!

28
00:01:10,458 --> 00:01:12,375
Come on,
what do you say, Kirihito?

29
00:01:12,458 --> 00:01:14,458
Look up "stoic"
in the dictionary,

30
00:01:14,541 --> 00:01:16,125
and you'll find Ushio's picture.

31
00:01:16,208 --> 00:01:18,416
So if he's excited,
it must be good.

32
00:01:19,583 --> 00:01:21,333
[KIRIHITO] Getting ready
for the final tournament

33
00:01:21,416 --> 00:01:24,000
is going to be demanding
physically and mentally.

34
00:01:25,083 --> 00:01:28,208
This may be their only chance
to relax before then.

35
00:01:28,291 --> 00:01:29,708
They might as well enjoy it.

36
00:01:30,875 --> 00:01:33,208
All right.
Let's go check out the castle.

37
00:01:33,291 --> 00:01:35,291
Yeah!

38
00:01:35,375 --> 00:01:37,125
Huh? Where'd the others go?

39
00:01:37,208 --> 00:01:38,416
[CHIHIRO scoffs]

40
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:39,958
Sightseeing doesn't really
do it for me,

41
00:01:40,041 --> 00:01:41,791
but food on the other hand.

42
00:01:41,875 --> 00:01:43,291
I second that.

43
00:01:43,375 --> 00:01:45,375
I'm dying to try Nagoya cuisine.

44
00:01:45,458 --> 00:01:46,958
[ALL]
Huh?

45
00:01:47,041 --> 00:01:48,916
[ALL groan]

46
00:03:19,416 --> 00:03:22,875
♪

47
00:03:22,958 --> 00:03:25,416
[MAN A]
High school sumo? Ha!

48
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:26,958
You mean those
national treasures

49
00:03:27,041 --> 00:03:29,166
the fans are besides
themselves over.

50
00:03:30,250 --> 00:03:31,625
[MAN B]
It's a bumper crop this year.

51
00:03:31,708 --> 00:03:34,333
We're talking a once
in a century pool of talent.

52
00:03:34,416 --> 00:03:36,916
Regardless, this year's
high school yokozuna

53
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,833
will most likely be
Tennoji again.

54
00:03:38,916 --> 00:03:41,166
Yeah, the kid's good,
don't get me wrong,

55
00:03:41,250 --> 00:03:43,625
but it'd be a mistake
to dismiss Yamatokuni's boy,

56
00:03:43,708 --> 00:03:45,291
Sosuke Kuze.

57
00:03:45,375 --> 00:03:47,625
Call it a hunch, but I think
he's got what it takes

58
00:03:47,708 --> 00:03:49,500
to make it
all the way to the top.

59
00:03:49,583 --> 00:03:51,791
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
One or two notable wrestlers

60
00:03:51,875 --> 00:03:54,458
doesn't automatically make it
a stand-out year.

61
00:03:54,541 --> 00:03:56,791
I would describe it differently.

62
00:03:56,875 --> 00:03:58,708
Given the number
of talented fighters,

63
00:03:58,791 --> 00:04:00,875
it's more like
the Sengoku era.

64
00:04:00,958 --> 00:04:02,000
-[camera shutter clicks]
-Hmm.

65
00:04:02,083 --> 00:04:03,416
[laughing]

66
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:04,833
I'm loving this!

67
00:04:04,916 --> 00:04:06,458
How could anyone pick
getting food

68
00:04:06,541 --> 00:04:08,250
over seeing a castle?

69
00:04:08,333 --> 00:04:12,250
I don't get why this is fun,
but at least you're enjoying it.

70
00:04:12,333 --> 00:04:14,208
By the way, what was the name
of the person

71
00:04:14,291 --> 00:04:15,583
who ordered its construction?

72
00:04:15,666 --> 00:04:17,208
Miyamoto Musashi?

73
00:04:17,291 --> 00:04:19,625
I'll be the first to admit
history's not my strong suit,

74
00:04:19,708 --> 00:04:21,958
but even I can tell
you're way off.

75
00:04:22,041 --> 00:04:24,375
I believe it was
Tokugawa Ieyasu.

76
00:04:24,458 --> 00:04:26,500
He had it built
for his ninth son.

77
00:04:26,583 --> 00:04:28,416
Yoshinao, if I remember.

78
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:30,875
Whoa! I'm impressed!

79
00:04:30,958 --> 00:04:33,041
You know, I've always been
an admirer of Yoshinao

80
00:04:33,125 --> 00:04:34,500
for how honest he was.

81
00:04:34,583 --> 00:04:36,875
[KIRIHITO] You two are
a couple of history buffs.

82
00:04:36,958 --> 00:04:39,833
[KEIJI] Come one, come all,
to the Sengoku period!

83
00:04:39,916 --> 00:04:42,375
I am the great Maeda Keiji!

84
00:04:42,458 --> 00:04:45,833
Who's brave enough
to challenge me to a sumo bout?

85
00:04:45,916 --> 00:04:47,458
-[CROWD murmuring]
-[grunts]

86
00:04:47,541 --> 00:04:48,791
Ooh! Pick me!

87
00:04:48,875 --> 00:04:51,541
I'm brave enough to fight
with you, Keiji!

88
00:04:51,625 --> 00:04:52,708
Hold up!

89
00:04:52,791 --> 00:04:54,208
You realize
he's an actor, right?

90
00:04:54,291 --> 00:04:55,958
So try not to kill him.

91
00:04:56,041 --> 00:04:59,000
[KEIJI]
Uh, this guy looks pretty eager.

92
00:04:59,083 --> 00:05:00,375
All right. You.

93
00:05:00,458 --> 00:05:02,666
-[BOY] Sure.
-Uh...

94
00:05:02,750 --> 00:05:05,500
Hate to tell you this, but Keiji
was pointing at me, dude.

95
00:05:05,583 --> 00:05:07,750
Not to mention that I raised
my hand before you did.

96
00:05:07,833 --> 00:05:09,208
Huh?

97
00:05:09,291 --> 00:05:11,875
I think it's pretty obvious
who he was picking.

98
00:05:11,958 --> 00:05:14,208
We made direct eye contact
and everything.

99
00:05:14,291 --> 00:05:16,208
Like you can even see anything!

100
00:05:16,291 --> 00:05:18,875
Look, I traveled all the way
from Chiba to be here!

101
00:05:18,958 --> 00:05:20,250
Sorry if I don't bow down,

102
00:05:20,333 --> 00:05:22,500
but I came here
all the way from Ishikawa.

103
00:05:22,583 --> 00:05:25,416
The same place
as the Maeda family.

104
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:26,666
Why don't you catch
the train home

105
00:05:26,750 --> 00:05:28,583
and go wrestle
someone more your style?

106
00:05:28,666 --> 00:05:29,833
Like a toddler, maybe.

107
00:05:30,916 --> 00:05:32,041
What was that?

108
00:05:32,125 --> 00:05:34,250
As a history buff,
I refuse to leave!

109
00:05:34,333 --> 00:05:37,083
And Keiji was from Yamagata,
not Ishikawa!

110
00:05:38,166 --> 00:05:39,375
[BOY]
All that aside,

111
00:05:39,458 --> 00:05:41,083
it'd be insulting
for someone short as you

112
00:05:41,166 --> 00:05:42,541
to fight against Keiji.

113
00:05:43,541 --> 00:05:45,666
Nobody should underestimate
a legend.

114
00:05:45,750 --> 00:05:48,000
And they should never
underestimate sumo.

115
00:05:49,250 --> 00:05:50,833
[KEI]
He's so big!

116
00:05:50,916 --> 00:05:53,166
[KIRIHITO] That's just gonna
piss off Hinomaru even more!

117
00:05:53,250 --> 00:05:54,458
What?

118
00:05:54,541 --> 00:05:56,625
Who here's looking down at sumo?

119
00:05:56,708 --> 00:05:58,458
I'm talking about you.

120
00:05:58,541 --> 00:05:59,625
Who else am I looking at?

121
00:05:59,708 --> 00:06:01,208
[chuckles]

122
00:06:01,291 --> 00:06:02,875
Well, if that's
the way you feel,

123
00:06:02,958 --> 00:06:04,458
then we should have a bout.

124
00:06:04,541 --> 00:06:07,166
And whoever wins gets the chance
to take on Keiji.

125
00:06:07,250 --> 00:06:11,166
Fine, but if you get hurt,
you can't hold me responsible.

126
00:06:11,250 --> 00:06:13,666
Well, this is
an unexpected development!

127
00:06:13,750 --> 00:06:16,666
But I'm all for it,
so go right ahead!

128
00:06:16,750 --> 00:06:19,125
♪

129
00:06:19,208 --> 00:06:21,000
[CHIZUKO]
Even when he's relaxing,

130
00:06:21,083 --> 00:06:22,875
somehow he ends up
sumo wrestling.

131
00:06:22,958 --> 00:06:24,791
I don't know
what's going to happen.

132
00:06:24,875 --> 00:06:26,375
I just hope no one gets injured.

133
00:06:26,458 --> 00:06:27,875
Get ready.

134
00:06:27,958 --> 00:06:29,375
Positions!

135
00:06:29,458 --> 00:06:32,833
♪

136
00:06:35,625 --> 00:06:36,750
[HINOMARU]
This guy.

137
00:06:36,833 --> 00:06:39,750
♪

138
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:46,125
[MAN A]
The Sengoku era, huh?

139
00:06:46,208 --> 00:06:48,250
For some reason,
you seem to be neglecting

140
00:06:48,333 --> 00:06:49,958
another very important name.

141
00:06:50,041 --> 00:06:52,166
If we're talking about promising
high school students,

142
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:53,375
you're absolutely right.

143
00:06:53,458 --> 00:06:55,375
It would be a mistake
to overlook him.

144
00:06:55,458 --> 00:06:57,875
I was thinking it wouldn't be
a terrible idea

145
00:06:57,958 --> 00:07:00,791
if we invited him to participate
in our little training session.

146
00:07:00,875 --> 00:07:01,750
His name?

147
00:07:01,833 --> 00:07:02,750
Now Spirit!

148
00:07:03,791 --> 00:07:05,750
[groans]

149
00:07:08,458 --> 00:07:11,875
Hands down he's the strongest
and closest to being a yokozuna.

150
00:07:11,958 --> 00:07:14,375
And don't forget
who his brother is.

151
00:07:14,458 --> 00:07:16,875
The ozeki Daikeisho.

152
00:07:16,958 --> 00:07:19,875
[KEI] He pushed Hinomaru
to the edge with one hit!

153
00:07:19,958 --> 00:07:21,291
[KIRIHITO]
How's this happening?

154
00:07:21,375 --> 00:07:22,666
And here of all places?

155
00:07:22,750 --> 00:07:24,541
[BOY] I figured
that'd be enough to finish you.

156
00:07:24,625 --> 00:07:25,541
Not bad.

157
00:07:26,708 --> 00:07:28,375
[grunts]

158
00:07:29,541 --> 00:07:31,250
[HINOMARU]
That thrust is insane!

159
00:07:31,333 --> 00:07:33,208
If it lands,
it'll take my head off!

160
00:07:34,333 --> 00:07:35,541
[KIRIHITO]
It's him.

161
00:07:35,625 --> 00:07:37,833
Reputed to be
the best high school sumo.

162
00:07:37,916 --> 00:07:41,208
Besides those strikes, he has
an ozeki for an older brother.

163
00:07:41,291 --> 00:07:43,875
National Treasure
Odenta Mitsuyo.

164
00:07:43,958 --> 00:07:45,708
AKA Tenma Hikage!

165
00:07:45,791 --> 00:07:47,625
Enough, Hinomaru!

166
00:07:47,708 --> 00:07:50,375
Now's not the time to try
and show off your strength!

167
00:07:50,458 --> 00:07:51,500
You're wrong.

168
00:07:51,583 --> 00:07:52,916
It's not about me!

169
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:53,958
Just the opposite!

170
00:07:54,041 --> 00:07:55,333
I wanna see what this guy's got!

171
00:07:56,833 --> 00:07:59,666
It's not just Tennoji and Kuze
I need to defeat.

172
00:07:59,750 --> 00:08:01,583
I need to see how far
my strength will take me

173
00:08:01,666 --> 00:08:02,625
at the finals!

174
00:08:04,416 --> 00:08:06,875
And you're the standard
of comparison!

175
00:08:06,958 --> 00:08:08,375
Odenta!

176
00:08:08,458 --> 00:08:09,291
[KEI]
He's got him!

177
00:08:09,375 --> 00:08:10,791
Do it!

178
00:08:10,875 --> 00:08:12,666
If I'm going to the finals,

179
00:08:12,750 --> 00:08:14,541
I need maximum strength!

180
00:08:14,625 --> 00:08:17,041
Hundred-Thousand Demon!

181
00:08:17,125 --> 00:08:18,541
Huh?

182
00:08:23,166 --> 00:08:24,583
What's this sinking feeling?

183
00:08:25,625 --> 00:08:26,875
Come to think of it,

184
00:08:26,958 --> 00:08:29,333
why'd he let me
grab him so easily?

185
00:08:29,416 --> 00:08:31,083
Is it a trap?

186
00:08:31,166 --> 00:08:33,791
If I throw him, will I lose?

187
00:08:33,875 --> 00:08:35,291
[TENMA]
What's wrong?

188
00:08:35,375 --> 00:08:37,083
I'm waiting to see your throw...

189
00:08:37,166 --> 00:08:38,833
Onimaru.

190
00:08:46,166 --> 00:08:48,541
Tenma! You idiot!
I found you!

191
00:08:48,625 --> 00:08:51,083
Who do you think you are,
competing in a bout

192
00:08:51,166 --> 00:08:53,333
when you didn't finish
cleaning the hall?

193
00:08:53,416 --> 00:08:55,541
Being a national treasure's
gone to your head!

194
00:08:55,625 --> 00:08:57,000
[TENMA]
Uh-huh.

195
00:08:57,083 --> 00:08:59,458
I can understand why you
would be thinking that...

196
00:08:59,541 --> 00:09:02,083
if I hadn't already
cleaned the hall.

197
00:09:02,166 --> 00:09:03,208
Captain!

198
00:09:03,291 --> 00:09:05,166
Maybe he'll listen
to you instead.

199
00:09:05,250 --> 00:09:07,041
I tried, but there's
no one home.

200
00:09:07,125 --> 00:09:08,625
[sighs]

201
00:09:08,708 --> 00:09:10,166
Looks like one
of our club members

202
00:09:10,250 --> 00:09:12,458
has been going around
starting trouble again.

203
00:09:13,458 --> 00:09:15,375
I realize you two were
in the middle of a bout,

204
00:09:15,458 --> 00:09:17,708
but you'll have to excuse us.

205
00:09:20,583 --> 00:09:23,541
Don't worry, you can finish
your fight during the finals

206
00:09:23,625 --> 00:09:26,166
and get the chance to use
that triple combo.

207
00:09:26,250 --> 00:09:27,125
[gasps]

208
00:09:28,375 --> 00:09:30,208
What the...
What did he mean?

209
00:09:30,291 --> 00:09:33,750
He made it sound as if they were
anticipating the combo.

210
00:09:34,958 --> 00:09:37,958
Hikage's stance was clearly
inviting a throw.

211
00:09:38,041 --> 00:09:40,750
It's been less than a week
since the Inter High.

212
00:09:40,833 --> 00:09:43,083
Did they already learn
how to counter it?

213
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:46,083
So, you've gotten the chance
to meet Onimaru in the flesh,

214
00:09:46,166 --> 00:09:47,375
what's your first impression?

215
00:09:47,458 --> 00:09:49,291
He's more cowardly
than I thought.

216
00:09:49,375 --> 00:09:50,416
Too bad.

217
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:52,375
But who can blame him?

218
00:09:52,458 --> 00:09:55,666
No one's anxious to watch their
technique get ripped apart.

219
00:09:55,750 --> 00:09:57,750
[slaps landing]

220
00:09:57,833 --> 00:10:01,000
[grunting, straining]

221
00:10:02,083 --> 00:10:04,333
-[OZEKI] Damn!
-[laughing]

222
00:10:04,416 --> 00:10:06,416
You didn't expect us to let
a bunch of high schoolers

223
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:08,125
beat us that easily, did you?

224
00:10:08,208 --> 00:10:11,583
♪

225
00:10:11,666 --> 00:10:13,083
-[door opens]
-Huh?

226
00:10:13,166 --> 00:10:15,125
[ALL WRESTLERS]
We thank you for your hard work!

227
00:10:16,166 --> 00:10:17,000
Hey, Ushio.

228
00:10:17,083 --> 00:10:18,041
Uh?

229
00:10:20,458 --> 00:10:23,208
[HINOMARU] Um, where are
we going, Saenoyama?

230
00:10:23,291 --> 00:10:25,291
[SAENOYAMA]
You're looking dejected.

231
00:10:26,833 --> 00:10:29,833
Does it have anything to do
with you hitting another wall?

232
00:10:29,916 --> 00:10:31,125
It'll be okay.

233
00:10:31,208 --> 00:10:33,791
The only thing I can do
is accept the fact

234
00:10:33,875 --> 00:10:35,583
my greatest weapon
won't bail me out

235
00:10:35,666 --> 00:10:37,625
during the finals tournament.

236
00:10:37,708 --> 00:10:40,000
It's getting to me a little,
to be honest.

237
00:10:40,083 --> 00:10:41,958
♪

238
00:10:42,041 --> 00:10:43,541
What are you talking about?

239
00:10:43,625 --> 00:10:45,000
The greatest weapon you possess

240
00:10:45,083 --> 00:10:46,958
is a heart
that refuses to give up.

241
00:10:47,041 --> 00:10:48,958
♪

242
00:10:49,041 --> 00:10:51,541
-[slaps landing]
-[WRESTLERS grunting]

243
00:10:51,625 --> 00:10:54,708
There's a reason the master
invited you to Nagoya.

244
00:10:54,791 --> 00:10:56,208
He believes
there's something here

245
00:10:56,291 --> 00:10:58,500
that will help you smash
through that wall of yours.

246
00:10:58,583 --> 00:11:02,416
The Suzugatake Faction,
which our stable belongs to.

247
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:03,958
More important,

248
00:11:04,041 --> 00:11:06,791
it represents
what you desire the most.

249
00:11:06,875 --> 00:11:08,875
An ordeal that will
make you stronger.

250
00:11:13,708 --> 00:11:15,916
[CHIZUKO] We can see
the whole sumo ring from here.

251
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:17,458
Let's set up the camera.

252
00:11:17,541 --> 00:11:19,375
[REINA]
Yeah. Sure.

253
00:11:19,458 --> 00:11:21,291
[grunting]

254
00:11:21,375 --> 00:11:24,500
Well, you and I
are officially creepers.

255
00:11:24,583 --> 00:11:26,375
He gave specific instructions.

256
00:11:26,458 --> 00:11:28,291
Your assignment is
to follow those two

257
00:11:28,375 --> 00:11:30,375
and record their training
using this.

258
00:11:30,458 --> 00:11:33,958
So how come those wrestlers
are training separately?

259
00:11:34,041 --> 00:11:36,416
It's almost like they think
they're better or something.

260
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:37,833
[CHIZUKO]
They are.

261
00:11:37,916 --> 00:11:39,833
Everyone in there has
a white mawashi belt,

262
00:11:39,916 --> 00:11:41,416
meaning they're all sekitori.

263
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:45,666
The sekitori are juryo ranked
sumo wrestlers and higher.

264
00:11:45,750 --> 00:11:48,750
They're considered the elite,
even among the pros.

265
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:49,708
Gah.

266
00:11:49,791 --> 00:11:51,416
You're like an encyclopedia.

267
00:11:51,500 --> 00:11:54,333
Didn't you only recently
get interested in sumo?

268
00:11:54,416 --> 00:11:57,041
I did some research
after joining the club.

269
00:11:57,125 --> 00:11:58,041
[REINA groans]

270
00:11:58,125 --> 00:11:59,750
I'm their manager, after all.

271
00:11:59,833 --> 00:12:01,333
I have to prove I'm useful.

272
00:12:01,416 --> 00:12:03,375
Thank you all
for your hard work!

273
00:12:07,458 --> 00:12:08,625
[gasps]

274
00:12:08,708 --> 00:12:11,125
I take it you're
the national treasure.

275
00:12:11,208 --> 00:12:13,625
The one Master Shibakiyama
keeps talking about.

276
00:12:13,708 --> 00:12:15,875
I'm Hinomaru Ushio!

277
00:12:15,958 --> 00:12:17,583
Thank you for having me!

278
00:12:17,666 --> 00:12:18,583
Yeah, yeah.

279
00:12:18,666 --> 00:12:20,250
Spare us the gratitude.

280
00:12:20,333 --> 00:12:21,541
What're you doing here?

281
00:12:21,625 --> 00:12:22,500
Uh...

282
00:12:23,666 --> 00:12:25,291
Isn't this
a critical time for us

283
00:12:25,375 --> 00:12:28,041
to prep for the upcoming
Nagoya Tournament?

284
00:12:28,125 --> 00:12:30,458
I thought we came here to get
some quality training in

285
00:12:30,541 --> 00:12:32,208
before the contest started.

286
00:12:32,291 --> 00:12:34,125
And now we have to babysit?

287
00:12:34,208 --> 00:12:35,250
Yeah.

288
00:12:35,333 --> 00:12:37,083
I don't remember
agreeing to this.

289
00:12:38,291 --> 00:12:40,541
[MIONISHIKI] In professional
sumo, rank is everything.

290
00:12:40,625 --> 00:12:44,083
Even if you are some bigshot kid
with a promising future,

291
00:12:44,166 --> 00:12:46,541
in this tent,
that means absolutely nothing.

292
00:12:46,625 --> 00:12:48,500
You don't even have a rank.

293
00:12:48,583 --> 00:12:50,541
To us, you're on the level
of a worm.

294
00:12:50,625 --> 00:12:51,500
Or lower.

295
00:12:52,958 --> 00:12:55,500
Well, I doubt they'll be
very welcoming.

296
00:12:55,583 --> 00:12:58,125
Huh? You didn't get
their approval?

297
00:12:58,208 --> 00:13:00,333
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
The sekitori are a proud bunch

298
00:13:00,416 --> 00:13:02,333
but for a legitimate reason.

299
00:13:02,416 --> 00:13:05,833
They got to where they are now
because they fought hard for it.

300
00:13:05,916 --> 00:13:08,250
You can't become one
if you don't have pride.

301
00:13:08,333 --> 00:13:10,166
The sumo ring is sacred ground

302
00:13:10,250 --> 00:13:11,416
where the only thing
that matters

303
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:12,958
is the wrestler's current rank.

304
00:13:13,958 --> 00:13:15,708
I led him to the straw bale.

305
00:13:15,791 --> 00:13:17,875
Whether he steps inside
is up to him.

306
00:13:17,958 --> 00:13:21,208
Entering and finding something
to grasp onto,

307
00:13:21,291 --> 00:13:24,875
that all depends
on Hinomaru's determination.

308
00:13:24,958 --> 00:13:26,416
♪

309
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:28,125
[SEKITORI A]
Not going to bail him out, Sae?

310
00:13:28,208 --> 00:13:30,375
[chuckles]
He'd thank you for it later.

311
00:13:30,458 --> 00:13:33,250
I assure you
nothing will make him leave.

312
00:13:33,333 --> 00:13:34,958
And I won't apologize
for bringing

313
00:13:35,041 --> 00:13:37,041
a bona-fide sumo wrestler
to you.

314
00:13:37,125 --> 00:13:39,250
♪

315
00:13:42,708 --> 00:13:45,125
Well, if I'm such an eyesore
to all of you,

316
00:13:45,208 --> 00:13:47,125
then just push me
out of the ring.

317
00:13:47,208 --> 00:13:48,708
Rank's everything, huh?

318
00:13:49,708 --> 00:13:51,083
Fine. So be it.

319
00:13:51,166 --> 00:13:52,958
All I need to do
is prove I'm worthy

320
00:13:53,041 --> 00:13:54,375
to be your training partner.

321
00:13:55,416 --> 00:13:57,208
How about you be the judge?

322
00:13:57,291 --> 00:13:59,333
Decide right now
what my rank should be.

323
00:13:59,416 --> 00:14:01,083
[chuckles softly]

324
00:14:01,166 --> 00:14:02,791
He's lost his mind.

325
00:14:02,875 --> 00:14:04,541
That guy looks super tough.

326
00:14:04,625 --> 00:14:05,500
Yes.

327
00:14:05,583 --> 00:14:07,166
His name's Mionishiki.

328
00:14:07,250 --> 00:14:08,750
A maegashira.

329
00:14:08,833 --> 00:14:10,500
Which means he's
a higher ranked sumo

330
00:14:10,583 --> 00:14:11,750
than Saenoyama.

331
00:14:11,833 --> 00:14:13,166
Oh wow, really?

332
00:14:13,250 --> 00:14:14,666
He's in trouble.

333
00:14:14,750 --> 00:14:17,500
Ushio's never managed
to defeat Saenoyama before.

334
00:14:17,583 --> 00:14:19,083
[REINA gasps]

335
00:14:19,166 --> 00:14:22,125
[HINOMARU] He's an
eighth-ranked maegashira.

336
00:14:22,208 --> 00:14:23,583
Can I defeat him?

337
00:14:23,666 --> 00:14:26,208
Focus! I need to give this
all I've got!

338
00:14:26,291 --> 00:14:28,250
If I don't, I'll regret it!

339
00:14:28,333 --> 00:14:29,916
No more disappointment!

340
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,875
♪

341
00:14:31,958 --> 00:14:33,416
[MIONISHIKI]
A spider stance.

342
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:34,458
What a child.

343
00:14:34,541 --> 00:14:36,041
Come.

344
00:14:37,041 --> 00:14:37,916
[REFEREE]
Spirit!

345
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:39,041
[HINOMARU grunts]

346
00:14:41,458 --> 00:14:44,375
[HINOMARU straining]

347
00:14:44,458 --> 00:14:47,375
Well, he's hanging on,
so that's something.

348
00:14:47,458 --> 00:14:49,916
[HINOMARU]
I keep having flashbacks

349
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,166
to my bout with Hikage.

350
00:14:52,500 --> 00:14:54,625
Why'd I stop myself mid-move?

351
00:14:54,708 --> 00:14:56,291
I was afraid.

352
00:14:56,375 --> 00:14:59,291
Scared of losing everything
I've accomplished up until now.

353
00:14:59,375 --> 00:15:01,791
Even though
it's practically nothing!

354
00:15:01,875 --> 00:15:02,750
No.

355
00:15:02,833 --> 00:15:04,750
Kill your fear!

356
00:15:04,833 --> 00:15:06,875
If I want this technique
to be successful,

357
00:15:06,958 --> 00:15:08,833
I have to put my life
on the line!

358
00:15:08,916 --> 00:15:11,208
Do not fear death!

359
00:15:11,291 --> 00:15:12,750
Step forward!

360
00:15:12,833 --> 00:15:14,208
Everything my body and spirit

361
00:15:14,291 --> 00:15:16,500
have to give needs
to go into this!

362
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:19,500
Hundred-Thousand Demon Drop!

363
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:21,583
[grunts]

364
00:15:21,666 --> 00:15:24,458
[SEKITORI gasp, murmur]

365
00:15:24,541 --> 00:15:25,541
Oh!

366
00:15:25,625 --> 00:15:27,291
Did that really just happen?

367
00:15:27,375 --> 00:15:29,291
-[CHIZUKO gasps]
-Hell yeah!

368
00:15:29,375 --> 00:15:31,416
[panting]

369
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:33,125
[HINOMARU]
It's not dead.

370
00:15:33,208 --> 00:15:35,583
The Hundred-Thousand Demon Drop
is still alive!

371
00:15:35,666 --> 00:15:38,916
How do you like
my junior apprentice?

372
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:41,791
Slightly more intimidating
than a worm, wouldn't you say?

373
00:15:41,875 --> 00:15:43,208
-[OLD MAN] So that's him.
-[BOTH gasp]

374
00:15:43,291 --> 00:15:46,166
The boy Kaoruyama's
been going on about.

375
00:15:46,250 --> 00:15:48,833
No one can deny,
he's one interesting kid.

376
00:15:48,916 --> 00:15:52,250
[HINOMARU] I just threw
a makuuchi sumo wrestler.

377
00:15:52,333 --> 00:15:54,916
Which means that sinking feeling
I had from my bout earlier

378
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,375
was only in my head!

379
00:15:56,458 --> 00:15:58,083
It isn't real!

380
00:15:58,166 --> 00:16:01,416
But the power of the
Hundred-Thousand Demon Drop is.

381
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:03,916
I can use the technique
against Hikage!

382
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:08,166
After watching you, I admit,
you have quite a unique style.

383
00:16:08,250 --> 00:16:09,875
What do you say we fight next?

384
00:16:09,958 --> 00:16:12,208
No, me.
You can wait.

385
00:16:12,291 --> 00:16:15,041
If he wanted their attention,
he's got it now.

386
00:16:16,083 --> 00:16:17,250
[HINOMARU]
Was I imagining it,

387
00:16:17,333 --> 00:16:18,708
or were they all
staring at me?

388
00:16:18,791 --> 00:16:20,291
Despite my doubts,

389
00:16:20,375 --> 00:16:22,541
it looks like he's earned
the right to train with us.

390
00:16:22,625 --> 00:16:26,250
He has, and yet, he's only
made it to the starting line.

391
00:16:26,333 --> 00:16:27,875
And now...

392
00:16:27,958 --> 00:16:30,291
welcome to the ultimate ordeal.

393
00:16:31,333 --> 00:16:33,125
[grunting]

394
00:16:33,208 --> 00:16:34,125
[BOTH]
Huh?

395
00:16:35,916 --> 00:16:37,458
Close.

396
00:16:37,541 --> 00:16:39,625
How about we just say we hit
the ground at the same time?

397
00:16:39,708 --> 00:16:41,416
Man, incredible technique.

398
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,291
[HINOMARU]
What's going on?

399
00:16:43,375 --> 00:16:44,625
Did I make a mistake?

400
00:16:44,708 --> 00:16:46,250
Hey.
I'm next up!

401
00:16:47,291 --> 00:16:48,416
[REFEREE]
Spirit!

402
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:49,750
[HINOMARU straining]

403
00:16:49,833 --> 00:16:51,208
[HINOMARU] This technique's
a triple combo

404
00:16:51,291 --> 00:16:52,791
that's all or nothing.

405
00:16:52,875 --> 00:16:55,333
If it's not done exactly right,
I lose.

406
00:16:55,416 --> 00:16:57,583
[grunting]

407
00:16:57,666 --> 00:17:00,166
-Ah!
-And done.

408
00:17:00,250 --> 00:17:01,208
[sighs]

409
00:17:01,291 --> 00:17:02,666
I guess that's that.

410
00:17:02,750 --> 00:17:05,041
[growling]

411
00:17:05,125 --> 00:17:06,958
Wait! Let's go again!

412
00:17:07,041 --> 00:17:08,791
One more time, please!

413
00:17:08,875 --> 00:17:10,916
[SEKITORI B] It won't matter,
but if you want.

414
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:12,666
♪

415
00:17:12,750 --> 00:17:13,916
[groans]

416
00:17:15,625 --> 00:17:16,833
He lost.

417
00:17:16,916 --> 00:17:18,000
Again.

418
00:17:18,083 --> 00:17:20,250
So was his first win
only a fluke?

419
00:17:20,333 --> 00:17:21,666
[HINOMARU]
Damn it.

420
00:17:21,750 --> 00:17:23,458
I think I had
the right timing there.

421
00:17:24,583 --> 00:17:26,416
[MIONISHIKI]
You don't want a rematch, do ya?

422
00:17:27,833 --> 00:17:29,291
[HINOMARU]
Mionishiki.

423
00:17:32,375 --> 00:17:34,166
[straining]

424
00:17:35,208 --> 00:17:36,750
[HINOMARU] This is the same
exact feeling I got

425
00:17:36,833 --> 00:17:38,333
when I was fighting Hikage.

426
00:17:38,416 --> 00:17:40,000
Like I'm sinking.

427
00:17:40,083 --> 00:17:41,000
Ignore it!

428
00:17:41,083 --> 00:17:42,083
There!

429
00:17:42,166 --> 00:17:43,458
So long!

430
00:17:44,458 --> 00:17:45,833
[groans]

431
00:17:45,916 --> 00:17:47,916
No. He's down.

432
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:50,000
Even Mionishiki defeated him.

433
00:17:51,541 --> 00:17:53,583
[MIONISHIKI] Now you know
the truth about your move.

434
00:17:53,666 --> 00:17:55,958
Sure, you caught me unaware
during our first bout

435
00:17:56,041 --> 00:17:58,625
because I'd never seen a
technique like that used before.

436
00:17:58,708 --> 00:18:00,083
It should be pretty obvious

437
00:18:00,166 --> 00:18:02,291
it's got more than its
fair share of weaknesses.

438
00:18:03,291 --> 00:18:05,750
We sekitori spend our days
analyzing moves

439
00:18:05,833 --> 00:18:07,583
and having our own dissected.

440
00:18:07,666 --> 00:18:09,208
We can't be fooled twice.

441
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:12,000
Thanks for
the amusing distraction,

442
00:18:12,083 --> 00:18:13,875
but it's time for us
to get back to training.

443
00:18:14,916 --> 00:18:16,375
[ALL SEKITORI]
Yeah.

444
00:18:16,458 --> 00:18:18,083
[CHIZUKO] Having his move
predicted like that

445
00:18:18,166 --> 00:18:19,250
must be humbling.

446
00:18:20,458 --> 00:18:21,916
He didn't do half bad

447
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:24,666
considering he fought
against elite sumo wrestlers.

448
00:18:24,750 --> 00:18:26,416
It's not like a high schooler
could size up

449
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:27,791
his moves that quick.

450
00:18:27,875 --> 00:18:29,875
While it's true professionals
have spent years

451
00:18:29,958 --> 00:18:32,000
learning to counter
various techniques,

452
00:18:32,083 --> 00:18:34,083
even a move
they've only seen once...

453
00:18:35,250 --> 00:18:38,000
what if a technique happens
to be recorded and analyzed

454
00:18:38,083 --> 00:18:39,541
over and over again?

455
00:18:39,625 --> 00:18:41,791
It's entirely possible
the exact same thing

456
00:18:41,875 --> 00:18:43,583
could happen during the finals.

457
00:18:43,666 --> 00:18:45,500
♪

458
00:18:45,583 --> 00:18:46,875
[gasps]

459
00:18:48,208 --> 00:18:49,458
[HINOMARU]
Both my spirit and body

460
00:18:49,541 --> 00:18:50,666
have reached their limits.

461
00:18:51,791 --> 00:18:54,333
My secret weapon's
been defeated.

462
00:18:54,416 --> 00:18:56,500
Does this mean
I can't get any stronger?

463
00:18:57,875 --> 00:19:01,166
So he really can't become
a yokozuna, then?

464
00:19:01,250 --> 00:19:04,833
I mean, his body, spirit,
and technique have all peaked.

465
00:19:04,916 --> 00:19:07,083
[scoffs]
Shows how much you know.

466
00:19:07,166 --> 00:19:08,458
[BOTH]
Huh?

467
00:19:08,541 --> 00:19:10,041
Technique's developed.

468
00:19:10,125 --> 00:19:12,333
An individual can spend
their entire lifetime

469
00:19:12,416 --> 00:19:13,833
refining a skill.

470
00:19:13,916 --> 00:19:15,791
There is no endpoint,
young lady.

471
00:19:17,458 --> 00:19:19,708
[HINOMARU]
Stop feeling sorry for yourself!

472
00:19:19,791 --> 00:19:22,125
Remember what Saenoyama said
to you, idiot!

473
00:19:23,958 --> 00:19:25,166
I can't give up!

474
00:19:25,250 --> 00:19:26,625
Think for a minute.

475
00:19:26,708 --> 00:19:28,583
There must be something
I can learn from the ozeki

476
00:19:28,666 --> 00:19:30,291
while I'm here!

477
00:19:30,375 --> 00:19:31,541
[OLD MAN]
Show me your face.

478
00:19:32,708 --> 00:19:35,625
You've got as much life in you
as a worm, but that'll do.

479
00:19:36,625 --> 00:19:37,750
Hasegawa!

480
00:19:37,833 --> 00:19:40,958
Huh? I don't go
by that name anymore.

481
00:19:41,041 --> 00:19:42,458
Uh!

482
00:19:42,541 --> 00:19:44,583
I'm going to borrow
this little demon for a while.

483
00:19:44,666 --> 00:19:46,458
What?

484
00:19:46,541 --> 00:19:48,541
[ALL SEKITORI]
Thank you for your hard work!

485
00:19:48,625 --> 00:19:50,625
Ugh. You're way too loud.

486
00:19:50,708 --> 00:19:52,375
[SAENOYAMA]
What's he doing here?

487
00:19:52,458 --> 00:19:54,875
Did Master Shibakiyama send him?

488
00:19:54,958 --> 00:19:57,000
The sekitori are acting strange.

489
00:19:57,083 --> 00:19:58,875
Is this old geezer important?

490
00:20:00,708 --> 00:20:01,916
[SAENOYAMA]
What're you waiting for?

491
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:03,250
You should go with him.

492
00:20:05,041 --> 00:20:07,625
I wish you and I
could swap places.

493
00:20:07,708 --> 00:20:09,208
I'm actually envious.

494
00:20:09,291 --> 00:20:10,750
[HINOMARU]
Huh?

495
00:20:10,833 --> 00:20:12,208
-[OLD MAN] Oh.
-[BOTH] Huh?

496
00:20:12,291 --> 00:20:14,083
[OLD MAN]
One of the girls can come too.

497
00:20:14,166 --> 00:20:16,250
You. The sassy one.

498
00:20:16,333 --> 00:20:17,666
-Let's go!
-What?

499
00:20:17,750 --> 00:20:18,750
You mean me?

500
00:20:20,833 --> 00:20:23,125
[HINOMARU] Excuse me, sir,
but where are we going?

501
00:20:23,208 --> 00:20:26,208
You'll protect me if this guy
turns out to be a weirdo.

502
00:20:27,625 --> 00:20:29,250
[HINOMARU] Look, I don't know
what's going on,

503
00:20:29,333 --> 00:20:31,750
but I don't have a lot of time
to waste while I'm in Nagoya.

504
00:20:32,916 --> 00:20:34,541
I was planning
on staying in the tent

505
00:20:34,625 --> 00:20:36,208
and training with the ozeki.

506
00:20:36,291 --> 00:20:37,625
-[OLD MAN] We've arrived.
-[BOTH gasp]

507
00:20:42,666 --> 00:20:44,583
This place is a mansion!

508
00:20:44,666 --> 00:20:46,416
Who exactly are you?

509
00:20:46,500 --> 00:20:47,416
Open it.

510
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:51,416
♪

511
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:53,666
-Ah!
-[BOTH coughing]

512
00:20:53,750 --> 00:20:55,000
[HINOMARU]
It's dusty!

513
00:20:55,083 --> 00:20:57,208
[OLD MAN] You want to train
with the ozeki?

514
00:20:57,291 --> 00:20:59,208
What's so great about them?

515
00:20:59,291 --> 00:21:00,750
None of them are champions.

516
00:21:00,833 --> 00:21:02,208
[HINOMARU gasps]

517
00:21:02,291 --> 00:21:05,166
[OLD MAN] But if you insist,
I'll let you decide.

518
00:21:05,250 --> 00:21:06,791
I'm a nice guy after all.

519
00:21:06,875 --> 00:21:09,083
You can either go back
to the tent

520
00:21:09,166 --> 00:21:10,500
and train with the others...

521
00:21:10,583 --> 00:21:11,791
[BOTH gasp]

522
00:21:11,875 --> 00:21:13,875
[OLD MAN]
...or, if you prefer,

523
00:21:13,958 --> 00:21:16,833
you can be instructed
by a former yokozuna instead.

524
00:21:17,916 --> 00:21:19,625
That's a big deal, right?

525
00:21:20,666 --> 00:21:22,458
[OLD MAN] We'll hone
that technique of yours

526
00:21:22,541 --> 00:21:25,125
until it finally becomes
an actual weapon.

527
00:21:25,208 --> 00:21:26,333
You idiot.

528
00:21:26,416 --> 00:21:29,291
[gasping]

529
00:23:00,416 --> 00:23:03,208
♪

530
00:23:03,291 --> 00:23:05,666
[OZEKI]
I can't get enough of this food!

531
00:23:05,750 --> 00:23:07,250
[YUMA]
The miso is the real star.

532
00:23:07,333 --> 00:23:09,333
I could eat this stuff forever!

533
00:23:09,416 --> 00:23:10,666
Me too!

534
00:23:10,750 --> 00:23:11,666
[JIRO]
Hmm?

535
00:23:11,750 --> 00:23:13,750
Are those the same kids?

536
00:23:13,833 --> 00:23:15,583
The Dachi High Sumo club

537
00:23:15,666 --> 00:23:18,875
that brought my brother's
restaurant to its knees?

538
00:23:18,958 --> 00:23:21,166
They broke him!

539
00:23:21,250 --> 00:23:24,625
Now's my chance to avenge
the family name!

540
00:23:24,708 --> 00:23:26,916
And for dessert, miso cake!

541
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:28,375
[JIRO]
Before you dig in,

542
00:23:28,458 --> 00:23:30,750
don't forget about
the miso topping!

543
00:23:30,833 --> 00:23:32,958
♪

544
00:23:33,041 --> 00:23:34,958
Is this how they serve food
in Nagoya?

545
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,916
[JIRO cackles]

